This paper is primarily focused on the development of a communication-efficient framework for vertical federated learning, which involves multiple parties collaborating to build models while preserving user privacy. This topic is closely related to machine learning (cs.LG), as well as cryptography and security (cs.CR), distributed computing (cs.DC), signal processing (cs.SI), and information theory (cs.IT).
